<div id="review_2104892395" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2104892395" />
    <a title="Sandy S" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6441069-sandy-s"><img alt="Sandy S" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1320628496p2/6441069.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2104892395?book_show_action=true">Aug 26, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sandy S" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sandy S" href="/user/show/6441069-sandy-s">Sandy S</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2104892395" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2344768123384316036">4.25 stars<br/><br/>ABOUT THE BOOK: Release Date November 2016<br/><br/>As the NSA gets a strong lead on one of the most prominent faces of ISIS, the Islamic State embarks on a bold course of action-an attack on American soil. Former Navy SEAL Adam Taylor, on a break between assignments for a global paramilitary security firm, is visiting his folks in his home town when he gets a new mission-provide security for a rock star who is in town for a St. Patrick&apos;s Day concert. Unknown to Adam, a team of American ISIS sol</span>
  <span id="freeText2344768123384316036" style="display:none">4.25 stars<br /><br />ABOUT THE BOOK: Release Date November 2016<br /><br />As the NSA gets a strong lead on one of the most prominent faces of ISIS, the Islamic State embarks on a bold course of action-an attack on American soil. Former Navy SEAL Adam Taylor, on a break between assignments for a global paramilitary security firm, is visiting his folks in his home town when he gets a new mission-provide security for a rock star who is in town for a St. Patrick's Day concert. Unknown to Adam, a team of American ISIS soldiers will soon arrive with a plan to wreak havoc on the Jersey Shore, and Adam will get caught up in a deadly game of wits between the terrorist menace and those tasked to protect the citizens of the homeland.<br /><br />••••••••••••••••<br /><br />REVIEW: Told from several third person perspectives WHEN THE REAPER COMES by John L. DeBoer is an action packed, suspense thriller focusing on home grown terrorism, ISIS supporters, and the ensuing operation that will see several government agencies outwit and outsmart a planned attack against American rock idol Brian Callahan whose anti-Muslim comments have caught the attention of the Islamic State. Enter former Navy SEAL and GSG (Global Security Guardian) specialist Adam Taylor whose latest assignment to protect Brian becomes complicated when three known ISIS sympathizers target Adam’s charge in a planned terrorist plot to take down as many people at the rock star’s concert. What ensues is the search for the people responsible as Adam and several security agencies of the US government coordinate a well-organized plan of attack.<br /><br />WHEN THE REAPER COMES is a story of good vs evil; of intrigue, mystery, action and suspense. John L. DeBoer weaves an infinitely detailed story line of fanaticism, religious faith, retaliation against American citizens, and the growing threat by ISIS-the Jihadist militant group that targets anyone and anything that stands in direct opposition to the Islamic State. There is a large ensemble cast of secondary and supporting characters including several members of the FBI and NSA, local and state police forces, US Marshalls, independent and private government security, ISIS militants, powerful financial Middle East politicians, and an assortment of former Vietnam Veterans itching to take down anyone targeting American citizens.<br /><br />From Iraq to New Jersey WHEN THE REAPER COMES gets up close and personal with a terrorist organization that is determined to destroy the American faith. The world has grown increasingly smaller when American citizens become targets of some of their own. The premise is engaging, intense and suspenseful; the action is thrilling and imaginative. My only concerns are the actions and intentions of one of the NSA agents-in reality the agent’s motives and behavior would have been flagged, investigated and not easily ignored in the face of ISIS and Islamic threats against the Western nations. I question the believability and our hero’s major lack of entanglement as to the potential threats against everyone concerned. At the very least, the agent’s connections are a big cause for alarm.<br /><br />Copy supplied for review<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="2344768123384316036" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

