        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2007891269" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3666715927544059475">When The Reaper Comes by John DeBoer, is a fitting name to call one of the terrorist group that seems to fester through our homeland murdering innocent people.<br/><br/> Adam is bodyguarding a musician who pissed off ISIS and now is coming full frontal on him which is located in Adams home town. This novel tells the story of Adam, a ex-navy seal, and his partner. They have to stay ahead and strong in the game,  there are many struggles ahead. There&apos;s also many style characters that attribute to either sid</span>
  <span id="freeText3666715927544059475" style="display:none">When The Reaper Comes by John DeBoer, is a fitting name to call one of the terrorist group that seems to fester through our homeland murdering innocent people.<br /><br /> Adam is bodyguarding a musician who pissed off ISIS and now is coming full frontal on him which is located in Adams home town. This novel tells the story of Adam, a ex-navy seal, and his partner. They have to stay ahead and strong in the game,  there are many struggles ahead. There's also many style characters that attribute to either sides of the fight. Adam recruits friends that have experience in securing defens. <br /><br />The book is full of twists and turns that'll keep you guessing. Asking yourselves, what's next? Our heroes find themselves in the most complicated conditions and choices to make, but will they make them wisely? You'll have to read it to find out.<br /><br /> This is a novel that will make you stop and think what's going on in the real world with ISIS. The situation in this novel could maybe come true, you never know. Reading the newspapers and watching the television about all the crazies out there on our home soil that actually join ISIS, anything is possible. <br /><br /><br /> I enjoyed this novel and had a hard time putting it down, if you like thrills, chill and action that'll keep you up wanting for more then I recommend this novel.</span>
