<div id="review_1874509600" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1874509600" />
    <a title="Maia Gomez" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/57035381-maia-gomez"><img alt="Maia Gomez" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1599066527p2/57035381.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1874509600?book_show_action=true">Jan 10, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Maia Gomez" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Maia Gomez" href="/user/show/57035381-maia-gomez">Maia Gomez</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1874509600" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11221932554339869441">Wow- this was one fast-paced and intense read that is actually almost terrifying since it&apos;s something that can actually happen any day now! The book stayed at a really steady pace and was full of action, twists and complex situations that really had me sitting on the edge of my seat the whole time! I loved how you get to see several different characters points of view at the same time, giving you every side of the story, which makes it all the more intense. The way the author executed everything</span>
  <span id="freeText11221932554339869441" style="display:none">Wow- this was one fast-paced and intense read that is actually almost terrifying since it's something that can actually happen any day now! The book stayed at a really steady pace and was full of action, twists and complex situations that really had me sitting on the edge of my seat the whole time! I loved how you get to see several different characters points of view at the same time, giving you every side of the story, which makes it all the more intense. The way the author executed everything to coordinate together was just masterful! You get to see things with Adam, an ex SEAL and current bodyguard for a patriotic rockstar as he tries to outhink the terrorists and figure out where they're most likely to strike next. You also get special insight with Amira, a NSA intelligence operator who thinks she's on a peaceful weekend getaway but instead ends up smack dab in the middle of conspiracy. Also, you get to be part of the terrorists point of view as they race around trying to make a strike, yet keep getting thwarted by Adam and his team. <br />I found this book wildly entertaining, yet very intense and suspenseful, keeping my mind racing to keep up with everything. Even though I'm not too huge on military and war type books, I thoroughly enjoyed every minute of this one and highly suggest it to anybody that wants a really good thrill! I think it's almost scary that something like this really could be happening right this second somewhere.....</span>
  <a data-text-id="11221932554339869441" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


