<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer17078020302853916687">After graduating from the University of Vermont College of Medicine, John L. DeBoer, M.D., F.A.C.S. completed his surgical training in the U.S. Army and then spent three years in the Medical Corps as a general surgeon. Thirty years of private practice later, he retired to begin a new career as a writer.<br/><br/>The father of two grown sons, he lives with his wife in North Carolina.</span>

